	<h1>Uncle Tom&#39;s Cabin</h1>
</header>

	<section id="film-detail-container">
		<img src="../static/images/m14.jpeg" alt="Film poster">

		<p><em>Uncle Tom&#39;s Cabin</em> is a silient historical drama film directed by Harry A. Polland, starring Margarita Fischer, Arthur Edmund Carewe, and George Siegmann .</p>

		<p>Carl Laemmle produced the film.</p>

		<p>
			It was released by Universal Pictures on November 4, 1927, with a runtime of 112 minutes.

			
				It had a budget of $1.5 million (estimated).
				When adjusted for inflation in 2023, that's approximately equivalent to $25.9 million. Box office numbers for the film could not be found.
			
		</p>

		<p>
			The film was written by Harvey F. Thew, A. P. Younger, and Walter Younger (titles), with Erno Rapee composing the filmâ€™s music. Charles Stumar and Jacob Kull oversaw cinematography, and Gilmore Walker, Daniel Mandell, Byron Robinson, and Ted Kent helped with editing the film.
		</p>

		<p><a href="https://archive.org/details/UncleTom_201902">View an archived version of <em>Uncle Tom&#39;s Cabin</em>.</a></p>

		<p><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Uncle_Tom%27s_Cabin_(1927_film)">View the Wikipedia entry for <em>Uncle Tom&#39;s Cabin</em>.</a></p>

		<p><a href="../index.html">Return to the list</a> to select a different film.</p>
	</section>

